@NODE Overview "Infos sur PetitChimiste"

@{b}PetitChimiste@{ub} is a 3D presentation tool for molecules using wireframe
or 3D synthesis. It allows you to do in addition some usefull calculations such
as the length or the angle between several atomes. In order to do this, this
program uses the @{"file format" LINK Format} of @{b}MOLEC3D@{ub}
CopyRight 1990 Stefan Abrecht with some variations ( a file saved
by PetitChimiste can no longer be loaded by MOLEC3D ). Morover PetitChimiste
can now load PC @{b}Alchemy@{ub} files filtered by CrossDos and @{b}PDB@{ub} files without their header.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "Installation"

  *********************************************************************
  WARNING: This version of PetitChimiste need the IXEMUL.LIBRARY >=41.3
               wich can be found on Aminet in /dev/gcc.
  *********************************************************************

1) Double-click on the Install-PetitChimiste icon.
   answer to the installation system.

2) Consult the @{"reference manual" LINK Reference}

3) If you have a powerfull graphic card, you can promote
   the PetitChimiste screen to higher resolutions with
   the screen promotion tool provided with your card.
   Take care to choose a display mode allowing square pixels.
   (I use NewMode 3.6 CopyRight Andreas Linnemann)

4) You can change the priority of the task and the interlacement of the screen
   via the tooltypes of the PetitChimiste.info file. See @{"FAQ" LINK FAQ}.

5) Run PetitChimiste, It will certainly be in the choosen language, @{"else..." LINK FAQ}

6) Load a molecule ...

@ENDNODE

@NODE FAQ "Questions and answers"

@{B}- My Amiga crashs when i run PetitChimiste from a SHELL!@{UB}
  You MUST run PetitChimiste ONLY by double-clicking on its icon.
  (Cause PetitChimiste needs a stack of 16ko)

@{B}- The multitasking activity is frozen!!!
- PetitChimiste is incredibly slow on my A4060PPC604!!!@{UB}
  You have probably played with the PRIORITY tooltype.
  Change it to PRIORITY=-1

@{B}- How could i have a non-interlaced screen?@{UB}
  Default tooltype is INTERLACED=YES.
  Change it to INTERLACED=NO

@{B}- Why PetitChimiste says that it can't open the screen?@{UB}
  You must have at least the AGA system to open this screen.

@{B}- My computer have 8MB of RAM and PetitChmiste says that it can't allocate 3.7MB of RAM!@{UB}
  PetitChimiste needs always large blocks of contiguous RAM. You certainly have
  to reboot your computer.

@{B}- Why PetitChimiste makes a sofware-failure on my AMIGA ?@{UB}
  You have certainly a @{b}68000@{ub} in your computer.

@{B}- Why the message "Can't open asl.library." ?@{UB}
  Your WorkBench have to be installed correctly.

@{B}- Why the message "Can't open locale.library." ?@{UB}
  Your WorkBench have to be installed correctly.

@{b}The following questions result from a bad "ŕ la main" installation @{ub}

@{B}- Why PetitChimiste explode on my computer running under WB2.1 ? I have all
  needed liraries and a big processor.@{UB}
  I have the same problem. I think it comes from the graphics.library < 3.0

@{B}- Why PetitChimiste isn't in the good language ?@{UB}
  You have to use the gived installation script..

@ENDNODE

